reviewText: I don't like the characters and the whole premise of the situation is creepy.
Best facial expressions on the planet!
all flintstones videos are GREAT am a BIG COLLECTOR . All the videos are good & fun to watch. Hope you enjoy them
This VHS was poor, couldn't see a whole episode. Very static and tape would jump around and hard to watch. It was more frustrating than anything.

My daughter really has enjoyed this video because Pebbles and Bamm-Bamm are actually speaking real words instead of baby talk.  She can't wait to get the other ones in this series!  Many familiar voice talents from other popular cartoons, also.  :)
What an entertainer.  You will laugh your self silly for 1 hour gaurenteed!  Its Dame Ednas slapstick humour at its best!  Buy it, you won't be sorry!
Interesting and intriguing.  Not sure it's the life for many, but these individuals seem to accept and thrive on it.

What. The.... What kind of idiot thought the premise of this show was a good idea? Creepy at best, terribly narrated and filmed at worst. Just keep searching and skip this whole series. Blech. As in, I want my $1.99 back.

An eclectic group of four people, quirky, contemplative episodes throughout with a narrator (as the video camera) that will remind one
somewhat of HAL 9000 in Kubrick's 2001 A Space Odyssey.
Love Dame Edna. Glad I was alive while she was performing.
Human experiment. Interesting and entertaining. Would like to see more.
finally proof i am not the only one!!
